<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[189,303,265,291]" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[189,1399,312,586]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
In the 
<typeStatus box="[268,320,312,338]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Thompson" authorityYear="1999" box="[470,905,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippina" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[470,905,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) philippina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is a headless specimen (
<specimenCount box="[1278,1322,312,338]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="female">
1 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1300,1322,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">♀</emphasis>
</specimenCount>
, “P.I.: Mindanao / 
<collectingRegion box="[332,454,347,373]" country="Philippines" name="Bukidnon" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Bukidnon</collectingRegion>
. 
<quantity box="[464,557,347,373]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.48" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="m" value="1480.0">1480 m</quantity>
. / Mt. Katanglad / 
<date box="[776,953,347,373]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" value="1959-10-27" valueMax="1959-10-31" valueMin="1959-10-27">27–31.X.1959</date>
”; “L.W. Quate / Collector” (
<potCollectionCode box="[1287,1375,347,373]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">BPBM</potCollectionCode>
)), see 
<figureCitation box="[239,336,383,409]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="27.[189,232,1891,1917]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,892,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[189,1399,892,1852]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view. A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) achaeta Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, holotype, Ƌ, Myanmar. B. S. (A.) achaeta, ♀, Myanmar. C. S. (A.) albolobata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Vietnam. D. S. (A.) amplistylus sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Philippines. E. S. (A.) apicalis Shiraki, 1930, Ƌ, Taiwan. F. S. (A.) apicalis, ♀, Taiwan. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830551/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
. This female is not 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Thompson" authorityYear="1999" box="[589,1028,383,409]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippina" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[589,1028,383,409]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) philippina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because the postpronotum is black (yellow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Thompson" authorityYear="1999" box="[392,600,418,445]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippina" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[392,407,419,445]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[422,451,418,444]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">(A</emphasis>
.
<emphasis box="[458,600,418,444]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">) philippina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the wing is hyaline (slightly infuscated in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Thompson" authorityYear="1999" box="[1130,1338,418,445]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippina" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[1130,1145,419,445]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1161,1189,418,444]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">(A</emphasis>
.
<emphasis box="[1197,1338,418,444]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">) philippina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and tergum V has the posterior margin straight (incised in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Thompson" authorityYear="1999" box="[850,1060,454,481]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippina" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[850,865,455,481]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[881,910,454,480]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">(A</emphasis>
.
<emphasis box="[917,1060,454,480]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">) philippina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). This specimen is possibly the female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[362,588,489,516]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplistylus" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[362,377,490,516]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[395,423,489,515]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">(A</emphasis>
.
<emphasis box="[431,588,489,515]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">) amplistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[598,695,489,515]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but as even the males of all the similar species are very difficult to distinguish from each other without reference to genitalia, the identity of this female remains doubtful.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
